  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Cavapoochon in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Cavapoochon is a cross of three breeds that are each on the HDB-approved list: the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel, the Bichon Frise, and the Toy Poodle. Crosses of approved small breeds are commonly accepted under HDB's rules, and the Cavapoochon's 4 to 6 kg size sits well within them. Every Cavapoochon we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase."
      bridge="Is a Cavapoochon HDB-friendly? Yes, as an approved-breed cross, and we place them in HDB homes. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
      citationLabel="Read HDB's guidelines on keeping pets"
